## Public Static Functions

### canRead() {#a91cc2902b5c82e2313c928a08a54597c}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>Expected&lt; FileType &gt; TextAPIReader::canRead (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/memorybufferref">MemoryBufferRef</a> InputBuffer)</>}
  labels = {["static"]}>
Determine whether input can be interpreted as TAPI text file.

This allows one to exit early when file is not recognized as TAPI file as opposed to <code>get</code> which attempts to full parse and load of library attributes.


<ParametersList title="Parameters">
<ParametersListItem name="InputBuffer">Buffer holding contents of TAPI text file.</ParametersListItem>
</ParametersList>

<SectionUser title="Returns">
The file format version of TAPI text file.
</SectionUser>
